Arsenal has confirmed that their defender, Tolaji Bola, has left the club to join League One side Rochdale on loan. Arsenal disclosed this in a statement via its official website on Thursday ahead of their Premier League clash with Man City on October 17. The statement read: “Tolaji Bola has joined League One side Rochdale on loan until the end of January 2021. “An Arsenal Academy graduate, the 21-year-old defender, has been at the club since the age of nine. “Everyone at Arsenal wishes Tolaji all the best for his time at Rochdale. “The loan is subject to the completion of regulatory processes.” Tolaji provided a strong presence in defence for Arsenal’s U23s side in the last two seasons.